UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 161
1 AN ACT relating to water fluoridation programs.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 211.190 is amended to read as follows:
4 The cabinet shall provide public health services, including:
5 (1) Administrative, consultative, technical, professional, and other services needed to
6 assist local health departments in the effective maintenance and operation of their
7 departments;
8 (2) Administrative, investigative, and clerical services required by the secretary of the
9 Cabinet for Health and Family Services, and may upon request provide these
10 services to any other agency of this Commonwealth authorized to control the
11 practice of any other healing art;
12 (3) Administration of grants, gifts, or contributions from the federal government, or
13 from other sources, for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of Pub. L. No.
14 725 (79th Congress, 2nd Session, chapter 958), or any other acts for the same or
15 similar purposes;
16 (4) Central registrations of births, deaths, and other vital records and the furnishing of
17 copies thereof to the general public in the manner prescribed by law;
18 (5) Statistical services, including the compilation, analysis, and maintenance of
19 statistics on matters related to public health, and may provide these services to
20 organizations and persons interested in public health;
21 (6) Education of the public concerning all matters relating to health, including the
22 publication and dissemination of health information, and the stimulation of citizen
23 support for the promotion and maintenance of high standards of public health
24 throughout the Commonwealth;
25 (7) Survey and study of the needs of medical and hospital facilities in the interest of the
26 health of the general public;
27 (8) Establishment, maintenance, and operation of public health laboratories and such
Page 1 of 2
