UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 161
1 branches thereof as may be needed;
2 (9) Establishment, maintenance, and operation of training facilities and schools for
3 employees of the cabinet and of local health departments;
4 (10) Tabulating, duplicating, and other ancillary services as are necessary to the
5 operation of the cabinet, including the keeping of adequate financial, personnel, and
6 other records; and
7 (11) (a) Establishment, maintenance, monitoring, and enforcement of optional water
8 fluoridation programs for the protection of dental health, participation in
9 which shall solely be decided by the governing body of a water system that is
10 subject to regulation by the cabinet.
11 (b) A fluoridation program for a water system in place on the effective date of
12 this Act shall continue until action is taken by its governing body to end its
13 participation.
14 (c) Any decision made by the governing body of a water system regarding its
15 participation in a water fluoridation program established under this
16 subsection shall be binding on all water systems whose water is supplied by
17 that water system.
18 (d) A governing body, a member or employee of a governing body, or any
19 public or private entity that may be held liable for the actions of a governing
20 body of a water system that makes a decision at any time under this
21 subsection to continue its participation, end its participation, or to begin
22 participation in an optional water fluoridation program shall be immune
23 from liability in any civil or criminal action for both its exercise of
24 discretion regarding the water system's optional participation in the
25 program and for any act or acts performed reasonably and in good faith to
26 implement its decision regarding its optional participation.
